 {"id":"asupersync-2b4jj.6.4","title":"Run dogfood rollout and define adoption-success metrics","description":"Pilot doctor_asupersync on asupersync itself, measure diagnosis time reduction, false-positive rates, and remediation success.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Dogfood rollout executes doctor_asupersync on asupersync plus at least one additional representative project profile under production-like workflow conditions.\\n2. Quantitative adoption metrics are captured: diagnosis time delta, false-positive/false-negative rates, remediation success rate, and operator confidence signals.\\n3. Rollout runbook includes structured logs, artifact links, issue classifications, and follow-up actions for every significant failure/regression.\\n4. Final rollout decision record explicitly references prerequisite quality gates (unit/e2e/logging/performance) and blocks closure if any gate is red.\\n5. Post-rollout summary is self-contained and actionable for future maintenance cycles.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"OliveCove","created_at":"2026-02-26T03:15:39.872101159Z","created_by":"CalmRaven","updated_at":"2026-03-05T21:51:53.385588251Z","closed_at":"2026-03-05T21:51:53.385564407Z","close_reason":"Cleared the rollout blocker by moving doctor orchestration E2E artifacts into staged output before publish. Validation: targeted matrix regression test passed via rch; standalone orchestration E2E passed; medium full-stack run1/run2 stage records now pass with published summaries. Repo-wide fmt/clippy still report unrelated pre-existing issues outside this slice.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["doctor-asupersync","metrics","rollout"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-2b4jj.6.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2b4jj.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-26T05:51:12.945448747Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-2b4jj.6.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-2b4jj.6","type":"